Docker user guide
yonghao.zhao@intel.com
Nov.23 2017

How to use the images
1.  copy the tar file (eg. mcu-bench.tar)
2.  make sure you have install docker  (sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install docker.io)
3.  sudo docker load –i mcu-bench.tar
4.  sudo docker images
5.  sudo xhost +
6.  sudo docker run –it –net=host  xxx(image id in step 4)
7.  Do your business
8.  Ctrl+D to quit

How to continue to use the container
1. sudo docker ps -a
2. sudo docker start xxx(container id in step1)
3. sudo docker attach xxx(container id in step1)

How to commit your changes to the docker (not necessary)
1.  sudo docker ps –a
2.  sudo docker commit xxxx(container id in step 1)  xxx(a new image name)
3.  sudo docker save –o xxx.tar  xxx(your image name)

Dependencies in the docker image:
1.  Basic tools: vim/git/nvm/node/curl/make/cmake/g++/gcc/pkg-config…
2.  MCU runtime dependencies: (install by ./init-all.sh --deps), in case you want to run mcu in the docker.
3.  FFmpeg, compiled with SDL to enable ffplay
4.  Opencv3.2 , compiled with opencv_contrib
5.  Vmaf
6.  PESQ
7.  Sox tools
8.  Openssl 1.0.2i (the dependencies of new QOStestclient libs)
